HEADWORD: Wrongly
<hw>Wrong"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a wrong manner; unjustly;
erroneously; wrong; amiss; <as>as, he judges <ex>wrongly</ex> of my
motives</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧And yet wouldst <xex>wrongly</xex>
win.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

